description.narrative: UNICEF generated a robust body of research to inform policymakers. Evidence generation was successfully used to place adolescents at the center of public-policy agenda, improve regulatory frameworks, budget allocations and access to health and education services, shape UNICEF response to Venezuelan migration crisis, better design policies on child protection, and enhance evaluation culture into public-policy- making processes. 26 research pieces include eight studies on Venezuelan migrant children; An Adolescent Well-Being Index; measurement of school climate conditions; menstrual hygiene management in schools; barriers to adolescent's health insurance, and a study on knowledge, attitudes and practices of public servants towards adolescents. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
